// src/eval/fixtures.ts
//
// The ground-truth eval set: 20 hand-written documents covering all 5
// documentType values. Written BEFORE ever running the harness, and
// deliberately NOT generated by an LLM — an LLM-generated "ground truth"
// would just be grading the pipeline against another LLM's opinion, which
// defeats the entire purpose of having ground truth at all (see
// docs/week-2-day-5.md's "Ground truth curation" section).
//
// Each type gets a mix of easy/unambiguous fixtures and a couple of
// genuinely ambiguous ones (documents that could plausibly be read as more
// than one type). The ambiguous ones matter most — they're where confidence
// calibration (v2's whole point) and reasoning-quality differences between
// v1 and v2 are actually likely to show up. An eval set of only easy cases
// would make v1 and v2 look identical, because there'd be nothing genuinely
// hard to tell them apart on.

